title: Alyssa Coxes CV
text:
cox24018@byui.edu | My LinkedIn



Learing HTML, CSS, and SQL


Python




2016-2020 Mountianside High School
August 2020 - April 2024 Brigham Young University, Provo
September 2024 - now Brigham Young University - Idaho, Rexburg

B.S. of Data Science




November 2020 - October 2021 Customer Service Associate, The Home Depot

Processed payments and returns with accuracy and efficiency.
Directed customers to appropriate departments for additional support.
Resolved customer complaints while prioritizing customer satisfaction and loyalty.
Answered customer telephone calls promptly to avoid on-hold wait times.

Sep 2021 - Oct 2021, May 2023 - Aug 2023, May 2024 - Sep 2024 Market Team, Hoffman Farms Store - Provided exemplary customer service by engaging with guests and guiding them seamlessly through the payment and checkout procedures, thereby enhancing their overall experience. - Demonstrated proficiency in operating POS systems while collaborating with team members to maintain fully stocked and visually appealing market displays. - Exhibited confidence in interactions with guests, with a focus on adeptly upselling products by imparting comprehensive knowledge about the farm, bakery, and merchandise offerings.



Jan 2019 - Mar 2020 AVID Tutor, Beaverton School District - Facilitated student-led tutorial groups of seven students - Established and maintained rapport with students - Determined from student notes and discussions the concepts that need to be taught or re-taught - Set an example of personal excellence and high expectations for all AVID students to follow - Communicate frequently and honestly with the AVID coordinator regarding student progress and areas of concern
Nov 2021 - Apr 2023 Volunteer, The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints - Set and accomplished weekly and long-term teaching and personal improvement goals. - Managed social media pages, overseeing content creation and posting schedules. Responsibilities included curating and posting engaging content and promptly responding to audience inquiries and messages.
